  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>All the guests can enjoy the use of the leisure club's heated swimming pool, sauna, whirlpool, Spa, excercise room, gymnasium and table tennis. There is also a solarium, two squash courts and a beauty salon, providing facial and body treatments. The hotel also offers car parking. There is a continual bus service between both Gatwick terminals and the hotel.
RH 07/03</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>The 4 star Mercure London Gatwick Airport is in an ideal location for business and holiday travellers, with the airport only 5 minutes away by shuttle service.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>The bedrooms are all very well equipped and have were refurbished in 2002. The rooms are large and spacious with all the facilities one would expect from a good four star hotel.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>It is a modern building two storey building with no particularly spectacular features.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The hotel offers a choice in dining venues; the more traditional pavilion restaurant and the bistro style cayley's offer International dishes.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The lobby is very large and modern, and furnished in marble and highly Polished gold fixtures and fittings. There is ample seating and the bistro is located at the end of the lobby.</Text>
  </Description>
